-------------------------------- AWS EC2 -----------------------------

EC2 => Elastic Compute Cloud

Elastic means in cloud whenever u need to expand your infrastructure they can elastically elongated and also come in the same old size in terms of infra. (Auto-Scale)

- To login in your EC2 instance via from our system to the remote location server we have to do with OpenSSH protocol (Client to connect with Server) -> secure-shell (ssh)
- Generate Private and Public keys
- Whom they have private key, they can request to the public key means the private key is on our system and from that we can request to the remote server. 


------------------- EC2 Networking 
If we want to 
- SSH : port 22
- HTTP : port 80
- HTTPS : port 443
